longBusinessSummary: Public Joint-Stock Company Federal Hydro-Generating Company - RusHydro, together with its subsidiaries, generates, transmits, distributes, and sells electricity and heat in Russia. It generates electricity from hydro, solar, wind, and geothermal energy. The company has an installed electricity generation capacity of 38.4 GW. It also engages in the research, engineering, construction, and energy retailing activities, as well as repair, modernization, and reconstruction of equipment and hydraulic structures. The company was founded in 2004 and is based in Moscow, Russia.
